Package com.wikischool.wikischool.main.utilities

Class LRUCache<K,​V>

java.lang.Object
com.wikischool.wikischool.main.utilities.LRUCache<K,​V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
LRUCacheInterface<K,​V>
public class LRUCache<K,​V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements LRUCacheInterface<K,​V>
Implementation of a Least Recently Used (LRU) cache. The LRU cache determines what entries can be deleted based on how relevant they are. Relevance is determined by how recently an entry was last used. Leaving the less relevant to be replaced. Relevance is implicit in this implementation based on an entries position in a linked list.
Author:
sean-harnett
